# AI Spaces Configuration

## Required Environment Variables

```bash
# JWT Secrets (change in production!)
JWT_SECRET=your-secret-change-in-production
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your-refresh-secret-change-in-production

# Server Configuration
AI_SPACES_PORT=3001
AI_SPACES_DATA=~/.ai-spaces
AI_SPACES_DB=${AI_SPACES_DATA}/ai-spaces.db
```

## Optional Environment Variables

```bash
# Open Registration
ALLOW_OPEN_REGISTRATION=false

# Bootstrap Admin (creates first admin user on startup)
BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_PASSWORD=secure-password

# Google OAuth (optional)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=GOCSPX-your-google-secret
GOOGLE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/api/auth/google/callback
```

## Google OAuth Setup

1. Go to [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
2. Create a new project or select an existing one
3. Enable the "Google+ API" or "People API"
4. Go to "Credentials" → "Create Credentials" → "OAuth 2.0 Client ID"
5. Application type: "Web application"
6. Authorized redirect URIs: `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/google/callback` (for local dev)
7. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret to your environment variables

### Docker Development

For Docker development, set the redirect URI to match your Docker setup:
```bash
GOOGLE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/api/auth/google/callback
```

The frontend runs on port 3000 (mapped from container port 80), and the Vite proxy forwards `/api` requests to the server.

### Production

In production, update the redirect URI to your production domain:
```bash
GOOGLE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=https://yourdomain.com/api/auth/google/callback
```

## Features

- **Password Authentication**: Traditional email/password login
- **Google OAuth**: Single sign-on with Google (when configured)
- **Account Linking**: Google OAuth automatically links to existing accounts with matching email
- **Registration Bypass**: Google OAuth sign-up is always allowed (email verified by Google), regardless of `ALLOW_OPEN_REGISTRATION`
